 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE A &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;#x2013;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3734-1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;SUMMARY OF SIGNIFICANT ACCOUNTING POLICIES&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1118&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;J &amp;amp; J Snack Foods Corp. and Subsidiaries (the Company) manufactures
 markets and distributes a variety of nutritional snack foods and beverages to the food service and retail supermarket industries. A summary of the significant accounting policies consistently applied in the preparation of the accompanying consolidated financial statements follows.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1120&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3722-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;1.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3723-1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Principles of Consolidation&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1122&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The consolidated financial statements include the accounts of J &amp;amp; J Snack Foods Corp. and its wholly-owned subsidiaries. Intercompany balances and transactions have been eliminated in the consolidated financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1124&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3724-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;2.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3725-1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Revenue Recognition&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1126&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We recognize revenue from our products when the products are shipped to our customers. Repair and maintenance equipment service revenue is recorded when it is performed provided the customer terms are that the customer is to be charged on a time and material basis or on a straight-line basis over the term of the contract when the customer has signed a service contract. Revenue is recognized only where persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists
 our price is fixed or estimable and collectability is reasonably assured. We record offsets to revenue for allowances
 end-user pricing adjustments
 trade spending
 coupon redemption costs and returned product. Customers generally do not have the right to return product unless it is damaged or defective. Our recorded liability for allowances
 end-user pricing adjustments and trade spending was approximately $11.7 million at September 26
 2015 and $11.5 million at September 27
 2014. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1128&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;All amounts billed to customers related to shipping and handling are classified as revenues. Our product costs include amounts for shipping and handling
 therefore
 we charge our customers shipping and handling fees at the time the products are shipped or when services are performed. The cost of shipping products to the customer is recognized at the time the products are shipped to the customer and our policy is to classify them as Distribution expenses. The cost of shipping products to the customer classified as Distribution expenses was $74
158
000
 $71
159
000 and $65
025
000 for the fiscal years ended 2015
 2014 and 2013

 serif&quot;&gt;During the years ended September 26

 we sold $25
536
000
 $22
826
000 and $22
836
000
 respectively
 of repair and maintenance service contracts in our frozen beverage business. At September 26

579

 respectively
 of which $70

    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3727-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;3.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3728-1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Foreign Currency&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1134&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Assets and liabilities in foreign currencies are translated into U.S. dollars at the rate of exchange prevailing at the balance sheet date. Revenues and expenses are translated at the average rate of exchange for the period. The cumulative translation adjustment is recorded as a separate component of stockholders&amp;#x2019; equity and changes to such are included in comprehensive income.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1136&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3729-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;4.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3730-1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Use of Estimates&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1138&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In preparing financial statements in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America
 management is required to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities
 the disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the financial statements
 and the reported amounts of revenues and expenses during the reporting period. Actual results could differ from those estimates.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1140&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3731-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;5.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3732-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Cash Equivalents&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1142&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Cash equivalents are short-term
 highly liquid investments with original maturities of three months or less.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1144&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3733-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;6.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3734-2&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Cash
 Accounts Receivable
 Customers
 Vendors and Employees Covered by Collective Bargaining Agreements Concentration&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1146&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We maintain cash balances at financial institutions located in various states. We have cash balances at two banks totalling approximately $84 million that is in excess of FDIC insurance of $250
000 per bank.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1148&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Financial instruments that could potentially subject us to concentrations of credit risk are trade accounts receivable; however
 such risks are limited due to the large number of customers comprising our customer base and their dispersion across geographic regions. We usually have approximately 15 customers with accounts receivable balances of between $1 million and $10 million.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1150&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We have several large customers that account for a significant portion of our sales. Our top ten customers accounted for 43%
 43% and 43% of our sales during fiscal years 2015
 2014 and 2013
 respectively
 with our largest customer accounting for 8% of our sales in 2015
 8% of our sales in 2014 and 8% of our sales in 2013. Three of the ten customers are food distributors who sell our product to many end users. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1152&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;About 25% of our employees are covered by collective bargaining agreements. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1154&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;None of our vendors supplied more than 10% of our ingredients and packaging in 2015
 2014 or 2013. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1156&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The majority of our accounts receivable are due from trade customers. Credit is extended based on evaluation of our customers&amp;#x2019; financial condition and collateral is not required. Accounts receivable payment terms vary and are stated in the financial statements at amounts due from customers net of an allowance for doubtful accounts. At September 26
 2015 and September 27
 2014
 our accounts receivables were $102
649
000 and $99
972
000 net of an allowance for doubtful accounts of $304
000 and $450
000. Accounts receivable outstanding longer than the payment terms are considered past due. We determine our allowance by considering a number of factors
 including the length of time trade accounts receivable are past due
 our previous loss history
 customers&amp;#x2019; current ability to pay their obligations to us
 and the condition of the general economy and the industry as a whole. We write off accounts receivable when they become uncollectible
 and payments subsequently received on such receivables are credited to the allowance for doubtful accounts.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1158&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3735-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;7.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3736-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Inventories&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1160&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Inventories are valued at the lower of cost (determined by the first-in
 first-out or weighted-average method) or market.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt; We recognize&amp;nbsp;abnormal amounts of idle facilities
 freight
 handling costs
 and spoilage&amp;nbsp;as charges of the current period.&amp;nbsp; Additionally
 we&amp;nbsp;allocate fixed production overhead to inventories&amp;nbsp;based on the normal capacity of&amp;nbsp;our production facilities.&amp;nbsp; We calculate normal capacity as the production expected&amp;nbsp;to be achieved over a number of periods or seasons under normal circumstances
 taking into account the loss of capacity resulting from planned maintenance.&amp;nbsp;This requires us to use judgment to determine when production is outside the range of expected variation in production (either abnormally low or abnormally high).&amp;nbsp; In periods of abnormally low production (for example
 periods in which there is significantly lower demand
 labor and material shortages exist
 or there is unplanned equipment downtime) the amount of fixed overhead allocated to each unit of production&amp;nbsp;is not increased.&amp;nbsp; However
 in periods of abnormally high production the amount of fixed overhead allocated to each unit of production is decreased to assure inventories are not measured above cost.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1162&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We review for slow moving and obsolete inventory and a reserve is established for the value of inventory that we estimate will not be used. At September 26
 2015 and September 27
 2014
 our reserve for inventory was $2
627
000 and $3
982
000
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1164&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3739-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;8.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3740-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Investment Securities&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1166&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We classify our investment securities in one of three categories: held to maturity
 trading
 or available for sale. Our investment portfolio at September 26
 2015
 consists of investments classified as held to maturity and available for sale. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The securities that we have the positive intent and ability to hold to maturity are classified as held to maturity and are stated at amortized cost. Investments classified as available for sale are reported at fair market value with unrealized gains and losses related to the changes in fair value of the securities recognized in accumulated other comprehensive income (loss). &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The mutual funds and preferred stock in our available for sale portfolio do not have contractual maturities; however
 we classify them as long term assets as it is our intent to hold them for a period of over one year
 although we may sell some or all of them depending on presently unanticipated needs for liquidity or market conditions. See Note C for further information on our holdings of investment securities.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1168&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3741-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;9.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3742-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Depreciation and Amortization&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1170&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Depreciation of equipment and buildings is provided for by the straight-line method over the assets&amp;#x2019; estimated useful lives. We review our equipment and buildings to ensure that they provide economic benefit and are not impaired.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1172&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Amortization of improvements is provided for by the straight-line method over the term of the lease or the assets&amp;#x2019; estimated useful lives
 whichever is shorter.&amp;nbsp; Licenses and rights
 customer relationships and non-compete agreements are being amortized by the straight-line method over periods ranging from 3 to 20 years and amortization expense is reflected throughout operating expenses.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1174&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Long-lived assets
 including fixed assets and amortizing intangibles
 are reviewed for impairment as events or changes in circumstances occur indicating that the carrying amount of&lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;the asset may not be recoverable.&amp;nbsp; Indefinite lived intangibles are reviewed annually for impairment. Cash flow and sales analyses are used to assess impairment. The estimates of future cash flows and sales involve considerable management judgment and are based upon assumptions about expected future operating performance.&amp;nbsp; Assumptions used in these forecasts are consistent with internal planning. The actual cash flows and sales could differ from management&amp;#x2019;s estimates due to changes in business conditions
 operating performance
 economic conditions
 competition and consumer preferences.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1176&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3743-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;10.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3744-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Fair Value of Financial Instruments&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1178&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The carrying value of our short-term financial instruments
 such as accounts receivables and accounts payable
 approximate their fair values
 based on the short-term maturities of these instruments.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1180&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3745-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;11.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3746-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Income Taxes&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1182&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We account for our income taxes under the liability method.&amp;nbsp; Under the liability method
 deferred tax assets and liabilities are determined based on the difference between the financial statement and tax bases of assets and liabilities as measured by the enacted tax rates that will be in effect when these differences reverse.&amp;nbsp; Deferred tax expense is the result of changes in deferred tax assets and liabilities.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1184&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Additionally
 we recognize a liability for income taxes and associated penalties and interest for tax positions taken&amp;nbsp;or expected to be taken in a tax return which are more likely than not to be overturned by taxing authorities (&amp;#x201c;uncertain tax positions&amp;#x201d;).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We have not recognized a tax benefit in our financial statements&amp;nbsp;for these uncertain tax positions.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;As of September 26
 2015 and September 27
 2014
 the total amount of gross unrecognized tax benefits is $334
000 and $315
000; respectively
 all of which would impact our effective tax rate over time
 if recognized.&amp;nbsp; We recognize interest and penalties related to income tax matters as a part of the provision for income taxes.&amp;nbsp; We had $199
000 of accrued interest and penalties as of September 26
 2015 and $180
000 as of September 27
 2014. We did not recognize any penalties and interest resulting from tax settlements in the years ended September 26
 2015 and September 27
 2014.&amp;nbsp; A reconciliation of the beginning and ending amount of unrecognized tax benefits is as follows&lt;/font&gt;: &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL2314&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 90%; MARGIN-LEFT: 9pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 10%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr id=&quot;TBL2314.finRow.1&quot;&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 85%&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;

  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1198&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Basic earnings per common share (EPS) excludes dilution and is computed by dividing income available to common shareholders by the weighted average common shares outstanding during the period. Diluted EPS takes into consideration the potential dilution that could occur if securities (stock options) or other contracts to issue common stock were exercised and converted into common stock.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1200&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1208&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;At September 26
 2015
 the Company has unrecognized compensation expense of approximately $3.3 million to be recognized over the next three fiscal years.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1210&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The fair value of each option grant is estimated on the date of grant using the Black-Scholes options-pricing model with the following weighted average assumptions used for grants in fiscal 2015
 2014 and 2013: expected volatility of 18.4% for fiscal year 2015
 expected volatility of 21.2% for fiscal year 2014 and 25.7% for fiscal year 2013: weighted average risk-free interest rates of 1.7%
 1.6% and 2.5%; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;dividend rate of 1.4%
 .9% and .8% and expected lives ranging &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;between 5 and 10 years for all years. An expected forfeiture rate of 19% was used for 2015
 20% was used for 2014 and 20% was used for 2013. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1212&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Expected volatility is based on the historical volatility of the price of our common shares over the past 49 to 55 months for 5 year options and 10 years for 10 year options. We use historical information to estimate expected life and forfeitures within the valuation model. The expected term of awards represents the period of time that options granted are expected to be outstanding. The risk-free rate for periods within the expected life of the option is based on the U.S. Treasury yield curve in effect at the time of grant. Compensation cost is recognized using a straight-line method over the vesting or service period and is net of estimated forfeitures.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1214&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;

 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;14.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3737-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;15.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3738-1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Commodity Price Risk Management&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1220&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Our most significant raw material requirements include flour
 packaging
 shortening
 corn syrup
 sugar
 juice
 cheese
 chocolate
 and a variety of nuts. We attempt to minimize the effect of future price fluctuations related to the purchase of raw materials primarily through forward purchasing to cover future manufacturing requirements
 generally for periods from 1 to 12 months. As of September 26
 2015
 we have approximately $68 million of such commitments. Futures contracts are not used in combination with forward purchasing of these raw materials. Our procurement practices are intended to reduce the risk of future price increases
 but also may potentially limit the ability to benefit from possible price decreases. Our policy is to recognize estimated losses on purchase commitments when they occur. At each of the last three fiscal year ends
 we did not have any material losses on our purchase commitments.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1222&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3739-2&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;16.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3740-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3741-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;17.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3742-1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Recent Accounting Pronouncements&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1231&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In May&amp;nbsp;2014
 the FASB issued guidance on revenue recognition which says that we should recognize revenue to depict the transfer of promised goods or services to customers in an amount that reflects the consideration which we expect to be entitled in exchange for those goods or services.&amp;nbsp; This guidance is effective for our fiscal year ending September 2019.&amp;nbsp; Early application is&amp;nbsp;permitted.&amp;nbsp; We will assess the impact this guidance will have on our consolidated financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1233&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In September 2015
 the FASB issued guidance on accounting for business combinations which require that an acquirer recognize adjustments to provisional amounts that are identified during the measurement period in the reporting period in which the adjustment amounts are determined. This guidance eliminates the requirement to retrospectively account for these adjustments. This guidance is effective for our fiscal year ended September 2018. Early adoption is permitted. We have not assessed the impact this guidance will have on our consolidated financial results.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1235&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In July 2015
 the FASB issued guidance which requires an entity to measure inventory at the lower of cost or net realizable value. Net realizable value is the estimated selling price in the ordinary course of business
 less reasonably predictable costs of completion
 disposal and transportation. This guidance will simplify the subsequent measurement of inventory
 as current guidance requires an entity to measure inventory at the lower of cost or market. Under current guidance
 market could be replacement cost
 net realizable value
 or net realizable value less an approximately normal profit margin. This guidance is effective for our fiscal year ended September 2018. Early adoption is permitted. We have not assessed the impact this guidance will have on our consolidated financial results.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL1245&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3717-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;18.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Revenue Recognition&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1126&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We recognize revenue from our products when the products are shipped to our customers. Repair and maintenance equipment service revenue is recorded when it is performed provided the customer terms are that the customer is to be charged on a time and material basis or on a straight-line basis over the term of the contract when the customer has signed a service contract. Revenue is recognized only where persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists
 our price is fixed or estimable and collectability is reasonably assured. We record offsets to revenue for allowances
 end-user pricing adjustments
 trade spending
 coupon redemption costs and returned product. Customers generally do not have the right to return product unless it is damaged or defective. Our recorded liability for allowances
 end-user pricing adjustments and trade spending was approximately $11.7 million at September 26
 2015 and $11.5 million at September 27
 2014. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1128&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;All amounts billed to customers related to shipping and handling are classified as revenues. Our product costs include amounts for shipping and handling
 therefore
 we charge our customers shipping and handling fees at the time the products are shipped or when services are performed. The cost of shipping products to the customer is recognized at the time the products are shipped to the customer and our policy is to classify them as Distribution expenses. The cost of shipping products to the customer classified as Distribution expenses was $74
158
000
 $71
159
000 and $65
025
000 for the fiscal years ended 2015
 2014 and 2013
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1130&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 of repair and maintenance service contracts in our frozen beverage business. At September 26

    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1138&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In preparing financial statements in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America
 management is required to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities
 the disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the financial statements

 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3731-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3733-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 serif&quot;&gt;Cash
 Accounts Receivable
 Customers
 Vendors and Employees Covered by Collective Bargaining Agreements Concentration&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1146&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We maintain cash balances at financial institutions located in various states. We have cash balances at two banks totalling approximately $84 million that is in excess of FDIC insurance of $250
000 per bank.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1148&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Financial instruments that could potentially subject us to concentrations of credit risk are trade accounts receivable; however
 such risks are limited due to the large number of customers comprising our customer base and their dispersion across geographic regions. We usually have approximately 15 customers with accounts receivable balances of between $1 million and $10 million.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1150&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We have several large customers that account for a significant portion of our sales. Our top ten customers accounted for 43%
 43% and 43% of our sales during fiscal years 2015
 2014 and 2013
 respectively
 with our largest customer accounting for 8% of our sales in 2015
 8% of our sales in 2014 and 8% of our sales in 2013. Three of the ten customers are food distributors who sell our product to many end users. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1152&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;About 25% of our employees are covered by collective bargaining agreements. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1154&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;None of our vendors supplied more than 10% of our ingredients and packaging in 2015
 2014 or 2013. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1156&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The majority of our accounts receivable are due from trade customers. Credit is extended based on evaluation of our customers&amp;#x2019; financial condition and collateral is not required. Accounts receivable payment terms vary and are stated in the financial statements at amounts due from customers net of an allowance for doubtful accounts. At September 26
 2015 and September 27
 2014
 our accounts receivables were $102
649
000 and $99
972
000 net of an allowance for doubtful accounts of $304
000 and $450
000. Accounts receivable outstanding longer than the payment terms are considered past due. We determine our allowance by considering a number of factors
 including the length of time trade accounts receivable are past due
 our previous loss history
 customers&amp;#x2019; current ability to pay their obligations to us
 and the condition of the general economy and the industry as a whole. We write off accounts receivable when they become uncollectible

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3735-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;7.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3736-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Inventories&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1160&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Inventories are valued at the lower of cost (determined by the first-in
 first-out or weighted-average method) or market.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt; We recognize&amp;nbsp;abnormal amounts of idle facilities
 freight
 handling costs
 and spoilage&amp;nbsp;as charges of the current period.&amp;nbsp; Additionally
 we&amp;nbsp;allocate fixed production overhead to inventories&amp;nbsp;based on the normal capacity of&amp;nbsp;our production facilities.&amp;nbsp; We calculate normal capacity as the production expected&amp;nbsp;to be achieved over a number of periods or seasons under normal circumstances
 taking into account the loss of capacity resulting from planned maintenance.&amp;nbsp;This requires us to use judgment to determine when production is outside the range of expected variation in production (either abnormally low or abnormally high).&amp;nbsp; In periods of abnormally low production (for example
 periods in which there is significantly lower demand
 labor and material shortages exist
 or there is unplanned equipment downtime) the amount of fixed overhead allocated to each unit of production&amp;nbsp;is not increased.&amp;nbsp; However
 in periods of abnormally high production the amount of fixed overhead allocated to each unit of production is decreased to assure inventories are not measured above cost.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1162&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We review for slow moving and obsolete inventory and a reserve is established for the value of inventory that we estimate will not be used. At September 26
 2015 and September 27
 2014
 our reserve for inventory was $2
627
000 and $3
982
000

  
  

 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3739-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;8.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3740-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Investment Securities&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1166&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We classify our investment securities in one of three categories: held to maturity
 trading
 or available for sale. Our investment portfolio at September 26
 2015
 consists of investments classified as held to maturity and available for sale. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The securities that we have the positive intent and ability to hold to maturity are classified as held to maturity and are stated at amortized cost. Investments classified as available for sale are reported at fair market value with unrealized gains and losses related to the changes in fair value of the securities recognized in accumulated other comprehensive income (loss). &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The mutual funds and preferred stock in our available for sale portfolio do not have contractual maturities; however
 we classify them as long term assets as it is our intent to hold them for a period of over one year


 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3741-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;9.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3742-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Depreciation and Amortization&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1170&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Depreciation of equipment and buildings is provided for by the straight-line method over the assets&amp;#x2019; estimated useful lives. We review our equipment and buildings to ensure that they provide economic benefit and are not impaired.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1172&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Amortization of improvements is provided for by the straight-line method over the term of the lease or the assets&amp;#x2019; estimated useful lives
 whichever is shorter.&amp;nbsp; Licenses and rights
 customer relationships and non-compete agreements are being amortized by the straight-line method over periods ranging from 3 to 20 years and amortization expense is reflected throughout operating expenses.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1174&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Long-lived assets
 including fixed assets and amortizing intangibles
 are reviewed for impairment as events or changes in circumstances occur indicating that the carrying amount of&lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;the asset may not be recoverable.&amp;nbsp; Indefinite lived intangibles are reviewed annually for impairment. Cash flow and sales analyses are used to assess impairment. The estimates of future cash flows and sales involve considerable management judgment and are based upon assumptions about expected future operating performance.&amp;nbsp; Assumptions used in these forecasts are consistent with internal planning. The actual cash flows and sales could differ from management&amp;#x2019;s estimates due to changes in business conditions
 operating performance
 economic conditions

  
  

 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3743-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;10.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3744-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Fair Value of Financial Instruments&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1178&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The carrying value of our short-term financial instruments
 such as accounts receivables and accounts payable
 approximate their fair values


 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3745-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;11.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3746-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Income Taxes&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1182&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We account for our income taxes under the liability method.&amp;nbsp; Under the liability method
 deferred tax assets and liabilities are determined based on the difference between the financial statement and tax bases of assets and liabilities as measured by the enacted tax rates that will be in effect when these differences reverse.&amp;nbsp; Deferred tax expense is the result of changes in deferred tax assets and liabilities.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1184&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Additionally
 we recognize a liability for income taxes and associated penalties and interest for tax positions taken&amp;nbsp;or expected to be taken in a tax return which are more likely than not to be overturned by taxing authorities (&amp;#x201c;uncertain tax positions&amp;#x201d;).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We have not recognized a tax benefit in our financial statements&amp;nbsp;for these uncertain tax positions.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;As of September 26
 2015 and September 27
 2014
 the total amount of gross unrecognized tax benefits is $334
000 and $315
000; respectively
 all of which would impact our effective tax rate over time
 if recognized.&amp;nbsp; We recognize interest and penalties related to income tax matters as a part of the provision for income taxes.&amp;nbsp; We had $199
000 of accrued interest and penalties as of September 26
 2015 and $180
000 as of September 27
 2014. We did not recognize any penalties and interest resulting from tax settlements in the years ended September 26
 2015 and September 27
 2014.&amp;nbsp; A reconciliation of the beginning and ending amount of unrecognized tax benefits is as follows&lt;/font&gt;: &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL2314&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 serif&quot;&gt;In addition to our federal tax return and tax returns for Mexico and Canada

  
  
  
  
  
  

 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3753-0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;12.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3754-0&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Earnings Per Common Share&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1198&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Basic earnings per common share (EPS) excludes dilution and is computed by dividing income available to common shareholders by the weighted average common shares outstanding during the period. Diluted EPS takes into consideration the potential dilution that could occur if securities (stock options) or other contracts to issue common stock were exercised and converted into common stock.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1200&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Our calculation of EPS is as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL2344S1&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr id=&quot;TBL2344S1.finRow.1&quot;&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 55%&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

     &lt;td id=&quot;TBL2344S1.finRow.1.amt.D4&quot; style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: bottom; BORDER-BOTTOM: #000000 1px solid; TEXT-ALIGN: center&quot; colspan=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fiscal Year Ended September 26
 2015&lt;/b&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td id=&quot;TBL2344S1.finRow.1.trail.D4&quot; style=&quot;BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none; PADDING-BOTTOM: 1px&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr id=&quot;TBL2344S1.finRow.2&quot;&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 55%&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td id=&quot;TBL2344S1.finRow.2.lead.D2&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;At September 26
 2015
 the Company has unrecognized compensation expense of approximately $3.3 million to be recognized over the next three fiscal years.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1210&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The fair value of each option grant is estimated on the date of grant using the Black-Scholes options-pricing model with the following weighted average assumptions used for grants in fiscal 2015
 2014 and 2013: expected volatility of 18.4% for fiscal year 2015
 expected volatility of 21.2% for fiscal year 2014 and 25.7% for fiscal year 2013: weighted average risk-free interest rates of 1.7%
 1.6% and 2.5%; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;dividend rate of 1.4%
 .9% and .8% and expected lives ranging &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;between 5 and 10 years for all years. An expected forfeiture rate of 19% was used for 2015
 20% was used for 2014 and 20% was used for 2013. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1212&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Commodity Price Risk Management&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1220&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Our most significant raw material requirements include flour
 packaging
 shortening
 corn syrup
 sugar
 juice
 cheese
 chocolate
 and a variety of nuts. We attempt to minimize the effect of future price fluctuations related to the purchase of raw materials primarily through forward purchasing to cover future manufacturing requirements
 generally for periods from 1 to 12 months. As of September 26
 2015
 we have approximately $68 million of such commitments. Futures contracts are not used in combination with forward purchasing of these raw materials. Our procurement practices are intended to reduce the risk of future price increases

 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 3%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3741-1&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;17.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 97%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA3742-1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Recent Accounting Pronouncements&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1231&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In May&amp;nbsp;2014
 the FASB issued guidance on revenue recognition which says that we should recognize revenue to depict the transfer of promised goods or services to customers in an amount that reflects the consideration which we expect to be entitled in exchange for those goods or services.&amp;nbsp; This guidance is effective for our fiscal year ending September 2019.&amp;nbsp; Early application is&amp;nbsp;permitted.&amp;nbsp; We will assess the impact this guidance will have on our consolidated financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1233&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In September 2015
 the FASB issued guidance on accounting for business combinations which require that an acquirer recognize adjustments to provisional amounts that are identified during the measurement period in the reporting period in which the adjustment amounts are determined. This guidance eliminates the requirement to retrospectively account for these adjustments. This guidance is effective for our fiscal year ended September 2018. Early adoption is permitted. We have not assessed the impact this guidance will have on our consolidated financial results.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1235&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In July 2015
 the FASB issued guidance which requires an entity to measure inventory at the lower of cost or net realizable value. Net realizable value is the estimated selling price in the ordinary course of business
 less reasonably predictable costs of completion
 disposal and transportation. This guidance will simplify the subsequent measurement of inventory
 as current guidance requires an entity to measure inventory at the lower of cost or market. Under current guidance
 market could be replacement cost
 net realizable value

 serif; WIDTH: 12%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: bottom; TEXT-ALIGN: right; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #cceeff&quot;&gt;647 &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td id=&quot;TBL2441.finRow.14.trail.4&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

    &lt;/tr&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE B &amp;#x2013; ACQUISITIONS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1258&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In October 2013
 we acquired the assets of New York Pretzel
 a manufacturer and distributor of soft pretzels selling primarily in the northeast to foodservice and retail locations.&amp;nbsp; Of the purchase price of $11.8 million
 $849
000 was allocated to intangible assets
 $7
716
000 was allocated to goodwill and $3
049
000 was allocated to property
 plant and equipment. This business had sales of about $4.3 million in our 2014 fiscal year included in the food service segment. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1260&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;In May 2014
 we acquired the stock of Philly&amp;#x2019;s Famous Water Ice
 Inc. (PHILLY SWIRL). PHILLY SWIRL
 located in Tampa
 FL
 produces frozen novelty products sold primarily to retail supermarket locations throughout the United States and to Canada with annual sales approximating $25 million.&amp;nbsp; The allocation of the purchase price of $17.4 million is $4.0 million to working capital
 $1.2 million to property
 plant and equipment
 $11.1 million to intangible assets
 $1.8 million to goodwill
 $4.0 million to deferred tax assets and $95
000 to other assets and $4.8 million to deferred tax liabilities. Sales of PHILLY SWIRL from the acquisition date to September 27
 2014 were $12.6 million and are included in the retail supermarket segment. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1262&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Acquisition costs of $269
000 for the New York Pretzel and PHILLY SWIRL acquisitions are included in other general expense in the consolidated statements of earnings for the year ended September 27
 2014.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1267&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The goodwill and intangible assets acquired in the business combinations are recorded at fair value.&amp;nbsp; To measure fair value for such assets

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE C &amp;#x2013; INVESTMENT SECURITIES&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1271&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;We have classified our investment securities as marketable securities held to maturity and available for sale. The FASB defines fair value as the price that would be received from selling an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants. As such
 fair value is a market-based measurement that should be determined based on assumptions that market participants would use in pricing an asset or liability. As a basis for considering such assumptions
 the FASB has established three levels of inputs that may be used to measure fair value:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;MTAB1275&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 72pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA1276&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Level 1&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA1277&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;observable input such as quoted prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;MTAB1280&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 72pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA1281&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Level 2&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA1282&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Observable inputs
 other than Level 1 inputs in active markets
 that are observable either directly or indirectly; and&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;MTAB1285&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 72pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA1286&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Level 3&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt; &lt;p id=&quot;PARA1287&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN-TOP: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Unobservable inputs for which there is little or no market data
 which require the reporting entity to develop its own assumptions.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1289&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Our marketable securities held to maturity and available for sale consist of investments in mutual funds
 preferred stock and corporate bonds. The fair values of mutual funds are based on quoted market prices in active markets and are classified within Level 1 of the fair value hierarchy.&amp;nbsp; The fair values of preferred stock and corporate bonds are based on quoted prices for identical or similar instruments in markets that are not active.&amp;nbsp; As a result
 preferred stock and corporate bonds are classified within Level 2 of the fair value hierarchy.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1292&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The amortized cost
 unrealized gains and losses
 and fair market values of our investment securities held to maturity at September 26
 2015 are summarized as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL2465&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; WIDTH: 95%; MARGIN-RIGHT: 5%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
     &lt;td style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1301&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The mutual funds seek current income with an emphasis on maintaining low volatility and overall moderate duration. We have reduced our investments in mutual funds over the past year&amp;nbsp;to $19 million at September 2015 from $128 million at September 2014. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The remaining unrealized losses at September 2015 of $827
000 are spread over 4 funds with total fair market value of $19.2 million. In 2015
 sales of mutual funds generated a realized loss of $4.3 million. The Fixed-to-Floating Perpetual Preferred Stock generate fixed income to call dates in 2018
 2019 and 2025 and then income is based on a spread above LIBOR if the securities are not called. The mutual funds and Fixed-to-Floating Perpetual Preferred Stock do not have contractual maturities; however
 we classify them as long term assets as it is our intent to hold them for a period of over one year
 although we may sell some or all of them depending on presently unanticipated needs for liquidity or market conditions. In the fourth quarter we invested $67 million in corporate bonds which generate fixed income to maturity dates in 2017 through 2021
 with $40 million maturing prior to the end of our fiscal year 2018. Our expectation is that we will hold the corporate bonds to their maturity dates and redeem them at our amortized cost. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA1302&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times

     &lt;td id=&quot;TBL2764.finRow.42.trail.5&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
